revision.text:
[[File:Beijing Planetarium new.jpg|thumb|The entrance to the Building B of the Beijing Planetarium]]
The '''Beijing Planetarium''' ({{zh|s=北京天文馆|t=北京天文館}}) is an astronomy museum in [[Beijing]], China.<ref name=planet>[http://www.bjp.org.cn/en/index.htm Introduction to Beijing Planetarium from its official website] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110104122748/http://www.bjp.org.cn/en/index.htm |date=January 4, 2011 }}</ref>

The Planetarium comprises two main buildings, Building A & B. Building A, which was built in 1957, contains the Celestial Theater, an Eastern Exhibition Hall and a Western Exhibition Hall. It was the first large-scale planetarium in China, and at one time the only planetarium in Asia.<ref name=planet/> Building B contains a digital space theater, 3D and 4D theaters, several exhibition halls and two observatories.<ref name=planet/>

